                             INSTALL TMUX CONFIG
                             ===================

STEP 0                          Prerequisite
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  Install tmux
    Ubuntu:
      sudo apt-get install tmux

    Fedora:
      sudo dnf install tmux
    
    MacOS(Homebrew):
      brew install tmux  


STEP 1                        Clone this repo 
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

    git clone https.//github.com/tianpai/tmuxConfig.git


STEP 2          Soft link or cp .tmux.conf to home directory
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  
  Change directory to tmuxConfig folder

    cd path/to/tmuxConfig/
  
  Soft link .tmux.conf to home directory

    ln -s tmuxConfig/.tmux.conf ~/.tmux.conf

  Or cpoy .tmux.conf to home directory

    cp tmuxConfig/.tmux.conf ~/.tmux.conf


STEP 2.1                       Source .tmux.conf
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 
    tmux source-file ~/.tmux.conf


STEP 3      Install TPM (Tmux Plugin Manager) and source .tmux.conf
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

    git clone https://github.com/tmux-plugins/tpm ~/.tmux/plugins/tpm


STEP 4                 Open tmux and install plugins
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Open terminal and type:
  tmux
  Press [prefix] + I (capital i, as in Install) to fetch the plugin.

  (the [prefix] for this config is Ctrl + a)


                                    USAGE
                                    =====

  Most of the key bindings are the same as default 

  IMPORTANT:                                           (same as default)
  preifx + I        Install plugins
  prefix + U        Update plugins
  prefix + r        Reload config file


  CUSTOM KEY BINDINGS:                                 (different from default)
  prefix + -        Split window vertically
  prefix + |        Split window horizontally
  prefix + up       Go to the pane above
  prefix + down     Go to the pane below
  prefix + left     Go to the pane on the left
  prefix + right    Go to the pane on the right


